		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The brick can be 20V too but if it only gives out 0.1A it will not be able to do anything. The brick you have probably does put out only about 500mA, and at that point voltage drop is so great it has problems keeping power regulators operational. There's maybe 6V left when you go and measure the brick output while the system runs.

		

